             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am a <rs id="t17781021-11-viclabel62" type="occupation">carman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17781021-11-victim132 t17781021-11-viclabel62"></join>. On last monday evening at about half after six o'clock as I was going down <placeName id="t17781021-11-crimeloc63">Poor Jury Lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17781021-11-crimeloc63" type="placeName" value="Poor Jury Lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17781021-11-crimeloc63" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17781021-11-off60 t17781021-11-crimeloc63"></join> with two baskets of sugar in a cart, which I had received from Mr. Goble in Church Lane, I saw the prisoner in my cart; he took out two loaves of sugar and I saw him give them to his partner, who ran away with them; he had another in his hand; I laid hold of his coat and secured him immediately; I have not since seen the other man, I dragged the prisoner by the collar, and drove my horse till I came to the constable's house.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17781021-11-person134">
                  WILLIAM
                   SMITH
               <interp inst="t17781021-11-person134" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17781021-11-person134" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17781021-11-person134" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am master of the cart. Skinner came home and told me he had lost two loaves of the sugar; he had one hundred and sixty loaves of sugar in the cart.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I am not guilty, I was not in the cart.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="177810210009"></xptr>For the Prisoner.</p>
